latestPosts.caption:
When @samirmodi, the Minister of Magic himself, graced the stage at the Cosmopolitan Blogger Awards, it wasn’t just about awards—it was about honouring excellence and celebrating talent. 🌟

Colorbar takes pride in showcasing emerging makeup artists and creators, offering them a platform to thrive and shine in collaboration with the #CosmopolitanBloggerAwards. 💄✨

Congratulations to all the incredible winners who are making waves in the world of beauty:
✨ Colorbar North Emerging Makeup Artist of the Year: @iamsahillllll
✨ Colorbar West Emerging Makeup Artist of the Year: @artistpoojabudhraja
✨ Colorbar East Emerging Makeup Artist of the Year: @makeupartist_prasenjit
✨ Colorbar South Emerging Makeup Artist of the Year: @parulkhattarmakeupartist
✨ LGBTQIA+ Makeup Artist of the Year: @cocoballucci_
✨ Celebrity Makeup Artist of the Year: @savleenmanchanda
✨ Artistry Makeup Artist of the Year: @alina_hasan_rizvi

Cheers to pushing limits, weaving magic, and crafting beauty beyond dreams! 🪄

#HouseOfSin #ColorbarxCosmo #CosmoBloggerAwards #MadeForMagic #Colorbar

latestPosts.caption:
As the great Aaron Siskind once said, “Photography is a way of feeling, of touching, of loving. What you have caught on film is captured forever… It remembers little things, long after you have forgotten everything.”
-
Having traveled extensively across the globe, I’ve curated a collection that holds a special place in my heart—moments from the bustling streets of cities, finding beauty in the rhythm of urban chaos. These photographs are a testament to the extraordinary within the ordinary.
-
While most of these treasures are still waiting to be unboxed, I am thrilled to share them with those who appreciate the art of storytelling through frames. If you’d like to bring one of these pieces into your space, feel free to reach out at samir.modi@gmail.com.
-
Until then, I encourage you to walk the streets, frame the moments, and capture the beauty around you. Because every frame is not just a photograph; it’s a memory etched forever! #photograhylovers #

True to its name, ‘Beautiful’ is not just a store; it’s an experience—and the people behind it are equally remarkable. I had the pleasure of meeting Mr. Narendra Chowdhary, the visionary owner, who personally introduced me to the finest offerings of his store. From luxury products to make-up and of course your brand @lovecolorbar, the selection here is curated to perfection. 
-
Mr. Chowdhary’s story is one of true grit and determination. Hailing from Rajasthan, he began his journey in Mumbai selling household items door-to-door. Today, he owns a flagship store in Khar, Mumbai—a favorite destination for film stars seeking makeup and daily essentials.
-
What makes ‘Beautiful’ truly unique is its ethos: they don’t just sell products; they sell emotions. Every customer leaves not only with high-quality items but with a smile and a sense of confidence. It’s an honor to have my brand available here, knowing that it’s part of such a heartfelt mission. After all, beauty is more than skin deep—it’s a feeling, an experience, and here, it’s a promise.
-
#samirmodi #colorbarcosmetics #lovecolorbar

latestPosts.caption: I would like to extend my warmest wishes for the new year to everyone. As we celebrate this new year, let us embrace it with renewed vigor and a commitment to excellence. May Lord Ganesh and Goddess Lakshmi bless you all, bringing light, happiness, and good health. Here’s to a bright future ahead! @lovecolorbar #celebration #recognition #meraki

Celebrating festivals with family is like reliving the magic of childhood—where every laugh, every moment, and every shared meal becomes a timeless memory. Sharing these moments with my BA’s adds an extra touch of magic.
-
Chandigarh, I still hold those performances and the love from all of you close to my heart. Thank you for making the most of the little time we had together. Our motto remains unchanged: we focus on emotions over products, because we truly care. #lovecolorbar💋 @lovecolorbar #madeformagic

My heartfelt gratitude goes out to all the wonderful people behind the counter at Colorbar. I want to thank you for standing by us and for your unwavering love and support towards me and the brand. It was truly a pleasure meeting you all, and hearing about your experiences and achievements.
Colorbar is all about creating magic in peoples life. That’s what I emphasize, instead of simply instructing to sell a product. Solve the customer’s problem and make them see and feel the magic when they use our products. That has been our goal since day one, and it will remain so until we reach the sky.

I loved playing bowling on the Nintendo with Viv, Bhabhi & Isha last night. Did not realise what I have been missing for so long. Thank you for such an amazing evening. Love You!
